I also have been working hard on personal matters (trying to find a job) and trying to write a technical safety book on prevention of cumulative trauma.  While doing this (and because of the book) I switched to the Devorak keyboard and have been re-learning how to type again (see the April issue of Discover Magazine).  It's almost like becoming a voluntary handicapped person--very frustrating initially, but it should have a great payoff later. So I have been somewhat distracted.<br><br>
Lien, I was serious about sticking it out and continuing to post here.  My observation is that there are not enough people contributing from your perspective.<br><br>
I hope that everyone is having a good weekend.  It's sunny here in Oregon on this Saturday morning.  Enjoy!
